Cloakfox: invoke pref migration + seed sync at BrowserGlue startup.

Two parent-process modules invoked at _beforeUIStartup:

  1. CloakfoxPrefMigration: one-shot mirror of legacy roverfox.s.*
     prefs (pre-cpp-first extension era) into cloakfox.s.*. Sets
     cloakfox.migration.v1.done=true on first run.

  2. CloakfoxSeedSync: continuous snapshot of cloakfox.container.*
     and cloakfox.* prefs into Services.ppmm.sharedData, plus a
     pref observer that keeps the snapshot live. JSWindowActor
     children read seeds via Services.cpmm.sharedData.get since
     user-set prefs in our custom namespaces don't auto-sync to
     content processes (verified empirically).

Order matters: migration first (so any roverfox.s.* legacy values
land in cloakfox.s.* / cloakfox.container.* before sync snapshots
them), then seed-sync.

--- a/browser/components/BrowserGlue.sys.mjs
+++ b/browser/components/BrowserGlue.sys.mjs
@@ -382,5 +382,24 @@

   _beforeUIStartup: function BG__beforeUIStartup() {
+    // Cloakfox: migrate legacy roverfox.s.* prefs (extension era) to
+    // cloakfox.s.* (cpp-first namespace), then snapshot all cloakfox
+    // seeds into sharedData so JSWindowActor children can read them.
+    try {
+      const { runCloakfoxPrefMigration } = ChromeUtils.importESModule(
+        "resource:///modules/CloakfoxPrefMigration.sys.mjs"
+      );
+      runCloakfoxPrefMigration();
+    } catch (_e) {
+      // Module missing on non-Cloakfox builds — ignore.
+    }
+    try {
+      const { initCloakfoxSeedSync } = ChromeUtils.importESModule(
+        "resource:///modules/CloakfoxSeedSync.sys.mjs"
+      );
+      initCloakfoxSeedSync();
+    } catch (_e) {
+      // Module missing on non-Cloakfox builds — ignore.
+    }
     lazy.SessionStartup.init();

     // check if we're in safe mode
